  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And our rabbi, who is very demanding when it comes to bar mitzvah speeches and usually has the kids rewrite them over and over again, he just let this fly.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But his whole speech was almost an accusation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I-- I think he-- he might have been talking for me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I feel it is extremely important that Judaism survive.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] But I have great ambivalence in-- in-- in seeing God up there as a all-kind figure, you know.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I-- I-- I have very mixed feelings.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When I go to synagogue, it makes me feel good, though, because I like the ritual and the closeness and the-- the-- you're sort of borne by-- by other people, you know, who are all in this together.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So that I-- I do like.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I once went back in Holland to the synagogue that-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] in the area where I lived, and I remember that I cried and cried and cried.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So some of it is-- is really a-- almost like a sad-- some of the part of religion is a sad remembrance of-- of things that are lost, rather than what-- what religion really means.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It has more to do with memory.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
